r saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret   De Evioth was born in 1283, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Robert  De Menzies about 1322, in Perthshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1364, in Weem, Perthshire, Scotland, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1283–1364":"1283–1364","1299–1346":"1299–1346","1323–1410":"1323–1410","1346":"1346","1323":"1323","1410":"1410","1299":"1299","1364":"1364","1283":"1283","about 1322":"umbes 1322","Busey Castle, Oyth, Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Weem, Perthshire, Scotland":"Weem, Perthshire, Scotland","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Scotland","Castle Menzies, Weem, Aberfeldy, Perth, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Weem, Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1283–1364":"1283–1364","1299–1346":"1299–1346","1323–1410":"1323–1410","1346":"1346","1323":"1323","1410":"1410","1299":"1299","1364":"1364","1283":"1283","about 1322":"noin 1322","Busey Castle, Oyth, Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Weem, Perthshire, Scotland":"Weem, Perthshire, Scotland","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, 